<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="517" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="16" pageNumber="517">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,832,1323]" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">
<keyLead pageId="16" pageNumber="517">
1 Head, thorax and abdomen dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[608,687,832,854]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[159,1421,188,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-25@2.[151,1436,181,1913]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Plesiochara japonica comb. nov.: A, dorsal habitus; B–C, median lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; D–E, ditto, ventral view; F, spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853871" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853871/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">Figs 1A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[697,729,832,853]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1930,1954]" captionTargetBox="[166,1421,290,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-68@7.[151,1436,273,1907]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Plesiochara nitida: A, dorsal habitus; B–C, median lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; D–E, ditto, ventral view; F, spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853877" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853877/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">4A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[737,770,832,854]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1868,1892]" captionTargetBox="[162,1430,198,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-25@10.[151,1436,181,1845]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Plesiochara inflexa sp. nov.: A, dorsal habitus; B–C, median lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; D–E, ditto, ventral view; F, spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853883" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853883/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">6A</figureCitation>
); dorsal surface of head and pronotum with reticulation; basal impression of abdominal tergites III–VII with pores small to medium................................................. 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,832,1323]" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">
<keyLead pageId="16" pageNumber="517">
- Head, thorax and abdomen reddish brown to light brown, darker in head and posterior part of abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[1211,1287,890,912]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1856,1880]" captionTargetBox="[183,1350,217,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[159,1429,181,1832]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Plesiochara rufula sp. nov.: A, dorsal habitus; B–C, median lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; D–E, ditto, ventral view; F, spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853893/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">Fig. 9A</figureCitation>
); dorsal surface of head and pronotum without reticulation; basal impression of abdominal tergites III–VII with pores large; legs longer (HTL/ PL = 1.41–1.54)......................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Inoue &amp; Maruyama, 2022" authorityName="Inoue &amp; Maruyama" authorityYear="2022" box="[1271,1354,949,971]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Plesiochara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="517" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufula" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1271,1354,949,971]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">P. rufula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1360,1436,949,970]" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1360,1436,949,970]" pageId="16" pageNumber="517" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="16" pageNumber="517">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,832,1323]" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">
<keyLead pageId="16" pageNumber="517">
2 Hypomera with posterior part of carina directed posteriorly almost paralleled to lateral margin (
<figureCitation box="[1128,1217,978,1000]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1381,1405]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,273,1352]" captionTargetId="figure-64@17.[151,1436,273,1358]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 12. Posterior part of hypomera:A, Plesiochara japonica comb. nov.; B, P. nitida; C, P. rufula sp. nov.; D–F, P. inflexa sp. nov.: D, Nagahashi, Otaru-shi, Hokkaido Pref.; E, Wakasugi forest, Nishiawakura-son, Okayama Pref.; F, near Dôsaka tunnel, Dôshi-mura, Yamanashi Pref." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853899" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853899/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">Fig. 12A</figureCitation>
); legs shorter (HTL/PL 1.13–1.20); median lobe of aedeagus with apical lobe thick; sclerites 1 strongly convex and curved laterally at posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[233,335,1037,1059]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[159,1421,188,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-25@2.[151,1436,181,1913]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Plesiochara japonica comb. nov.: A, dorsal habitus; B–C, median lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; D–E, ditto, ventral view; F, spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853871" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853871/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">Fig. 1B–E</figureCitation>
); spermatheca with capsule spherical.......................................... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Inoue &amp; Maruyama" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Sharp" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[1213,1320,1038,1059]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Plesiochara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="517" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonica" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1213,1320,1038,1059]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">P. japonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1326,1436,1037,1058]" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1326,1436,1037,1058]" pageId="16" pageNumber="517" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,832,1323]" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">
<keyLead pageId="16" pageNumber="517">
- Hypomera with posterior part of carina directed to posterolateral corners obliquely (
<figureCitation box="[1062,1211,1066,1088]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1381,1405]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,273,1352]" captionTargetId="figure-64@17.[151,1436,273,1358]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 12. Posterior part of hypomera:A, Plesiochara japonica comb. nov.; B, P. nitida; C, P. rufula sp. nov.; D–F, P. inflexa sp. nov.: D, Nagahashi, Otaru-shi, Hokkaido Pref.; E, Wakasugi forest, Nishiawakura-son, Okayama Pref.; F, near Dôsaka tunnel, Dôshi-mura, Yamanashi Pref." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853899" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853899/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">Fig. 12B, D–F</figureCitation>
); legs longer (HTL/PL 1.27–1.47); median lobe of aedeagus thin; sclerites 1 not as above (
<figureCitation box="[864,965,1096,1118]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1930,1954]" captionTargetBox="[166,1421,290,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-68@7.[151,1436,273,1907]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Plesiochara nitida: A, dorsal habitus; B–C, median lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; D–E, ditto, ventral view; F, spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853877" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853877/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">Fig. 4B–E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[974,1032,1096,1118]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1868,1892]" captionTargetBox="[162,1430,198,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-25@10.[151,1436,181,1845]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Plesiochara inflexa sp. nov.: A, dorsal habitus; B–C, median lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; D–E, ditto, ventral view; F, spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853883" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853883/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">6B–E</figureCitation>
); spermatheca with capsule ovate (
<figureCitation box="[1363,1433,1096,1118]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1930,1954]" captionTargetBox="[166,1421,290,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-68@7.[151,1436,273,1907]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Plesiochara nitida: A, dorsal habitus; B–C, median lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; D–E, ditto, ventral view; F, spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853877" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853877/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">Fig. 4F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[226,253,1125,1147]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1868,1892]" captionTargetBox="[162,1430,198,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-25@10.[151,1436,181,1845]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Plesiochara inflexa sp. nov.: A, dorsal habitus; B–C, median lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; D–E, ditto, ventral view; F, spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853883" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853883/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">6F</figureCitation>
)................................................................................................. 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="16" pageNumber="517">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,832,1323]" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">
<keyLead pageId="16" pageNumber="517">
3 Hypomera with carina not curved inward at posterior end (
<figureCitation box="[799,887,1154,1176]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1381,1405]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,273,1352]" captionTargetId="figure-64@17.[151,1436,273,1358]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 12. Posterior part of hypomera:A, Plesiochara japonica comb. nov.; B, P. nitida; C, P. rufula sp. nov.; D–F, P. inflexa sp. nov.: D, Nagahashi, Otaru-shi, Hokkaido Pref.; E, Wakasugi forest, Nishiawakura-son, Okayama Pref.; F, near Dôsaka tunnel, Dôshi-mura, Yamanashi Pref." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853899" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853899/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">Fig. 12B</figureCitation>
); legs longer (HTL/PL = 1.35–1.47); median lobe of aedeagus with apical lobe weakly curved dorsally at apex, curved ventrally at base (
<figureCitation box="[1004,1107,1184,1206]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1930,1954]" captionTargetBox="[166,1421,290,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-68@7.[151,1436,273,1907]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Plesiochara nitida: A, dorsal habitus; B–C, median lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; D–E, ditto, ventral view; F, spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853877" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853877/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">Fig. 4B–E</figureCitation>
); spermatheca with capsule longer than chamber (
<figureCitation box="[369,440,1213,1235]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1930,1954]" captionTargetBox="[166,1421,290,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-68@7.[151,1436,273,1907]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Plesiochara nitida: A, dorsal habitus; B–C, median lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; D–E, ditto, ventral view; F, spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853877" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853877/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">Fig. 4F</figureCitation>
)........................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sawada" authorityYear="1990" box="[1357,1436,1213,1235]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Plesiochara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="517" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitida">
<emphasis box="[1357,1436,1213,1235]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">P. nitida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,832,1323]" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">
<keyLead pageId="16" pageNumber="517">
- Hypomera with carina curved inward at posterior end in most cases (
<figureCitation box="[897,1015,1242,1264]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1381,1405]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,273,1352]" captionTargetId="figure-64@17.[151,1436,273,1358]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 12. Posterior part of hypomera:A, Plesiochara japonica comb. nov.; B, P. nitida; C, P. rufula sp. nov.; D–F, P. inflexa sp. nov.: D, Nagahashi, Otaru-shi, Hokkaido Pref.; E, Wakasugi forest, Nishiawakura-son, Okayama Pref.; F, near Dôsaka tunnel, Dôshi-mura, Yamanashi Pref." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853899" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853899/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">Fig. 12D–E</figureCitation>
); legs rather longer (HTL/PL = 1.27–1.40); median lobe of aedeagus with apical lobe entirely curved ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[890,994,1272,1294]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1868,1892]" captionTargetBox="[162,1430,198,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-25@10.[151,1436,181,1845]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Plesiochara inflexa sp. nov.: A, dorsal habitus; B–C, median lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; D–E, ditto, ventral view; F, spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853883" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853883/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">Fig. 6B–E</figureCitation>
); spermatheca with capsule almost as long as chamber (
<figureCitation box="[322,393,1301,1323]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1868,1892]" captionTargetBox="[162,1430,198,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-25@10.[151,1436,181,1845]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Plesiochara inflexa sp. nov.: A, dorsal habitus; B–C, median lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; D–E, ditto, ventral view; F, spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853883" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853883/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">Fig. 6F</figureCitation>
)........................................................................ 
